claim.claim-text:
9. A method for setting a transmission and reception frequency bandwidth in a radio communication system defining a plurality of frequency bandwidths, comprising:
providing capability for processing a transmission frequency bandwidth of a predetermined value greater than a minimum frequency bandwidth in the plurality of frequency bandwidths, as a transmission frequency bandwidth of a pilot channel and a data channel for an uplink, to every mobile terminal accommodated in the radio communication system,
wherein the radio communication system is a same system corresponding to a standard of Evolved Universal Terrestrial Radio Access (E-UTRA);

selecting a transmission frequency bandwidth of the pilot channel and the data channel within a range of a maximum transmission frequency bandwidth of the mobile terminal according to a frequency bandwidth used by the base station in the radio communication system;
setting the transmission frequency bandwidth of an uplink collision permissible channel transmitted from any mobile terminal in the radio communication system to be a minimum transmission frequency bandwidth of the plurality of frequency bandwidths.

15. A base station used in a radio communication system defining a plurality of frequency bandwidths, comprising:
a reception unit configured to receive pilot channels of a first frequency bandwidth from a plurality of mobile terminals;
a measurement unit configured to measure channel states on a frequency axis based on the received pilot channels;
a transmission band assignment unit configured to assign a transmission band of a data channel using a second frequency bandwidth narrower than the first frequency bandwidth to each mobile terminal based on the measurement result; and
a control unit configured to set the transmission frequency bandwidth of an uplink collision permissible channel transmitted from any mobile terminal in the radio communication system to be a minimum transmission frequency bandwidth of the plurality of frequency bandwidths.
